2. Backwash the softener and add a solution of (Insert appropriate food contact dilution from table or list) {{EquivalentDilution}} of this product to the brine tank well. {{BrineTank}} {{Note}}

SPLD_InsertTextDU.Text: The brine tank must have water in it to permit the solution to be carried into the softener.
Note: Standard system capacity is 48 gal.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: 3. Proceed with the normal regeneration or interrupt the cycle after the brining step and let the softener soak for a minimum of 1 minute.

4. Backwash the softener with potable water to make sure all sanitizing solution is thoroughly rinsed from the unit before returning the system to service. Return system to service. Follow the manufacturer?s directions for re-installation of new pre-filters, membrane element and post filter.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: Reverse Osmosis (RO) Units ?
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: Sanitization must occur after initial installation, after the system is serviced and periodically during its use.

1. Turn off RO system, drain storage tank and remove membrane element and pre-filters. Put membrane element in a plastic bag so it remains wet. Do not use this product to sanitize the membrane element. Membrane element must be sterilized separately.
2. Tank must be washed with a compatible detergent and rinsed with potable water before sanitizing. (Note: Use this direction only if applicable.)
3. Fill empty pre-filter housing with a solution of {{#AppropriateDilution}} {{EquivalentDilution}} of this product and turn on raw water. {{Note}}.

SPLD_InsertTextDU.Text: Note: Standard system capacity is 1 to 2 gal.
(Insert appropriate food contact dilution from table or list)

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: 4. After holding tank is full, let system stand idle for a minimum of 1 minute. Turn off water. Drain holding tank.

5. Before the system is put back into service, flush system with potable water to assure sanitizing solution is rinsed thoroughly from system. Return unit{{s}} to normal operation. Follow the manufacturer?s directions for re-installation of new pre-filters, membrane element and post filter.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseCategory.Name: ANIMAL PREMISES
SPLD_DirectionsForUseCategory.Title: ANIMAL PREMISES
SPLD_DirectionsForUseCategory.ReviewerNote: The following statement will be used on all labels with use directions for animal premises except terrariums, small animal cages, and reptile tanks directions.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: Prior To Use
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Prior to use of this product, remove all animals {{Poultry}} and feeds from {{{PremisesAreas}}, animal transportation vehicles {{Trucks,Cars}}, and enclosures {{Coops,Crates,Kennels,Stables}}. Remove all litter, droppings and manure from floors, walls and surfaces of barns, pens, stalls, chutes and other surfaces of facilities and fixtures occupied or traversed by animals. Empty all troughs, racks and other feeding and watering appliances. Thoroughly clean surfaces with soap or detergent and rinse with water.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: ANIMAL PREMISE DISINFECTANT/VIRUCIDE*
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: FOR USE AS AN ANIMAL PREMISE DISINFECTANT/VIRUCIDE*:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Apply a use solution of 3 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water {(or equivalent use dilution)} to disinfect hard, non-porous surfaces with a sponge, brush, cloth, {by immersion}, {mechanical spray device,} {{hand pump} coarse pump or trigger spray device}. Immerse all halters and other types of equipment used in handling and restraining animals, as well as forks, shovels, and scrapers used for removing litter and manure in the use solution. For spray applications, spray 6-8 inches from surface. Do not breathe spray. Treated surfaces must remain wet for 10 minutes. Ventilate buildings, coops and other closed spaces. Do not house [{animals} {poultry} {livestock}] or employ equipment until treatment has been absorbed, set or dried. Thoroughly scrub all treated feed racks, troughs, automatic feeders, fountains and waterers and other treated equipment which can contact food or water with soap or detergent, and rinse with potable water before reuse.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: HATCHERIES
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: HATCHERIES:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Use to treat hatchers, setters, trays, racks, carts, sexing tables, delivery trucks and other hard surfaces. Use 3 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water. Leave all treated surfaces wet for 10 minutes or more. Allow to air dry. VEHICLES: Clean all vehicles including mats, crates, cabs, and wheels with water and this product. Use 3 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water. Apply use solution to treat all vehicles. Leave treated surfaces wet for 10 minutes or more. Allow to air dry.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: DRESSING/RENDERING PLANT
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: DRESSING {/RENDERING} PLANT:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Disinfect equipment, utensils, walls and floors in poultry and animal dressing plants. Disinfect offal rooms, exterior walls and loading platforms of dressing plants. Cover or remove all food and packaging materials. Remove all heavy soils prior to application. Saturate all surfaces with a solution of [{3 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water} {(or equivalent use dilution)} and scrub to loosen all soils. Surfaces must remain wet for 10 minutes, and then be thoroughly rinsed with potable water before operations are resumed.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: TERRARIUM AND SMALL ANIMAL CAGE
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: TERRARIUM AND SMALL ANIMAL CAGE AND CAGE FURNITURE DISINFECTION:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: {Animals frequently defecate on hot rocks and other hard, non-porous cage furniture items inside your terrarium. This can result in high bacteria and ammonia levels that can lead to possible infection/disease in your animals. When used regularly, this product can eliminate these high bacteria/ammonia levels in your cage and on your cage furniture items.} (Do not use on porous rocks, hot rocks, and driftwood.)

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: 1. Remove all animals.

2. Thoroughly clean all surfaces and objects {caves, cage furniture, feeding and watering dishes, and appliances} including the substrate in the terrarium or cage with soap or detergent and rinse with water.

3. Saturate all hard, non-porous surfaces {such as floors, walls, cages and other washable hard, non-porous surfaces} with the disinfecting and virucidal* solution of 3 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water {(or equivalent use dilution)} {(450 ppm active)} so as to wet thoroughly.

4. Apply by cloth, mop, brush, sponge, auto scrubber or mechanical spray device {{hand pump} coarse pump or trigger spray device} or by immersion. For spray applications, spray 6-8 inches from surface. Do not breathe spray. Rub with brush, cloth, or sponge. For smaller surfaces, use a trigger spray bottle to spray all surfaces with solution.
5. Allow surfaces to remain wet for a period of 10 minutes.
6. Saturate gravel as above and let stand for 10 minutes. Place in bucket of clean water and swirl for 15-30 seconds. Thoroughly air dry before returning to terrarium.
7. Thoroughly scrub all treated surfaces (except gravel) with soap or detergent and rinse with potable water before reuse.
8. Do not return animals to the habitat until it is dry and ventilated.
9. Clean terrarium at least once weekly or more as needed. Change cloth, sponge or towels frequently to avoid redeposition of soil.
10. Prepare a fresh solution daily or more often if use solution becomes visibly soiled or dirty.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: REPTILE TANK
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: REPTILE TANK CLEANING AND DISINFECTION DIRECTIONS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Remove all reptiles from the [{enclosure} {tank}] prior to cleaning and disinfecting. Remove all litter or drippings from surfaces. Empty all equipment used for feeding or watering reptiles. Thoroughly clean all surfaces with soap or detergent and rinse with water.  Apply disinfecting and virucidal* solution of 3 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water {(or equivalent use dilution)} {(450 ppm active)} {to hard, non-porous surfaces of the enclosure {tank}}. Apply by cloth, mop, brush, sponge, auto scrubber, mechanical spray device, {{hand pump} coarse pump or trigger spray device} or by immersion until thoroughly wet. For spray applications, spray 6-8 inches from surface. Do not breathe spray. Allow surfaces to remain wet for 10 minutes. Wipe dry {with a paper towel}. Rinse all surfaces that come in contact with food with potable water before reuse. Allow the enclosure {tank} to ventilate for a minimum of 10-15 minutes before replacing the reptiles. Prepare a fresh solution daily or when visibly dirty.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: DAIRIES, BEVERAGE AND FOOD PROCESSING PLANTS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: DIRECTIONS FOR FOGGING IN DAIRIES, BEVERAGE AND FOOD PROCESSING PLANTS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Prior to fogging, food products and packaging material must be removed from the room or carefully protected. After disinfecting, fog desired areas using 1 quart per 1000 cubic feet of room area with a solution containing 1.5 oz. of product per gal. of water {(1,200 ppm active)} {(or equivalent use dilution)}. Wear a dust mist respirator when mixing the use solution and pouring it into the fogging apparatus. Vacate the area of all personnel during fogging and for a minimum of 2 hours after fogging and a minimum of 4 air exchanges (ACH) per hour in the facility. All food contact surfaces must be sanitized with an EPA approved food contact sanitizer solution prior to use.  All food contact surfaces must be thoroughly rinsed with potable water prior to sanitizing.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: HATCHERY ROOMS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: TREATMENT OF HATCHERY ROOMS USING FOGGING DEVICES:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Remove all animals and feed from premises, vehicles and enclosures. Remove all litter and manure from floors, walls and surfaces of the room to be treated. Empty all troughs, racks and other feeding and watering appliances. Thoroughly clean all surfaces with soap or detergent and rinse with water. Close room off so fog is confined to room to be treated. Mix 140 oz. of this product per 2.5 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}}. Wear a dust mist respirator when mixing the use solution and pouring it into the fogging apparatus. Insert the nozzle of the fogger through a suitable opening into the room. With the setting in maximum output, fog for one minute for each 4000 cubic feet of space in the room. Under no circumstances will a room be entered by anyone within 2 hours of actual fogging and a minimum of 4 air exchanges (ACH) per hour in the facility. When fogging is completed ventilate buildings and other closed spaces. Do not house {{Livestock}} or employ equipment until treatment has been absorbed or dried. Thoroughly clean all treated surfaces with soap or detergent and rinse with water.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: INCUBATORS AND HATCHERS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: TREATMENT OF INCUBATORS AND HATCHERS USING FOGGING DEVICES:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Only for treatment of setters and hatchers after poultry/chicks/eggs have been removed. Not for treatment of hatchers which contain chicks/eggs. Mix 14.5 oz. of this product per gal. of water {(or equivalent use dilution)}. Wear a dust mist respirator when mixing the use solution and pouring it into the fogging apparatus. Fog 3-8 oz. of this into setters and hatchers immediately after transfer. Repeat daily in setters and every 12 hours in hatchers. Discontinue hatcher treatments at least 24 hours prior to pulling the hatch. Do not allow people to contact or breathe this fog. It is acceptable to fog setters and hatchers with a 1.1 oz. of this product per gal. of water solution {(or equivalent use dilution)} on an hourly or every other hour basis. If this is done, fog for 30-90 seconds once per hour or once every two hours. When fogging is complete, ventilate buildings, and other closed spaces. Do not house livestock or employ equipment until treatment has been absorbed or dried. Thoroughly scrub all treated feed racks, mangers, troughs, automatic feeders, fountains and waterers, and other treated equipment with soap or detergent, and rinse with potable water before reuse. Under no circumstances will a room be entered by anyone within two hours of the actual fogging and a minimum of 4 air exchanges (ACH) per hour in the facility.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: GROOMING IMPLEMENTS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: FOR USE AS A DISINFECTANT, VIRUCIDE* OF GROOMING CLIPPERS, HAIR CLIPPERS, ELECTRIC SHEARS, BARBER/SALON SHEERS AND OTHER IMPLEMENTS {{InstrumentsTools}}:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: {{RemoveParticles}} Immerse pre-cleaned barber/salon tools such as combs, brushes, {{PlasticRollers}} razors, {{ClipperTrimmerBlades}}, {{Tweezers}} manicure/pedicure tools, scissors, and other salon instruments and tools in a use solution of 3 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}} for at least 10 minutes. Rinse thoroughly and dry before use. Prepare a fresh solution daily or when visibly dirty.

SPLD_InsertTextSectionDU.Text: Remove hair, dandruff and dust particles prior to disinfecting the blades. {{Clipper}} with a use solution. Do not spray on the clipper case or drip into clipper housing.
Turn the clipper off occasionally during use and spray between the teeth of blades
While clipper/shear is running, hold in the downward position and spray

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: FOOTBATHS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: FOR USE AS A DISINFECTANT, VIRUCIDE* OF HARD, NON-POROUS SURFACES IN FOOTBATHS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: To remove body oils, dead tissue, soil and all other buildups or organic matter on surfaces after using the footbath, drain the water and thoroughly clean all surfaces with soap or detergent, then rinse with water. Apply a use solution of 3 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water  {(or equivalent use dilution)} on all surfaces with a brush, cloth, mop, sponge, {{PumpSpray}}. Brush or swab thoroughly and allow solution to stand for 10 minutes. For spray applications, spray 6-8 inches from surface. Do not breathe spray. After the unit has been thoroughly disinfected, rinse all surfaces with fresh water. The unit is then ready for reuse.

SPLD_InsertTextSectionDU.Text: {{Pump}} coarse pump or trigger spray device

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: BARBER/SALON NON-FOOD CONTACT SURFACES
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: SANITIZER DIRECTIONS FOR NON-FOOD CONTACT SURFACES IN BARBER/SALON FACILITIES

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: BARBER/SALON INSTRUMENTS AND TOOLS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: TO SANITIZE [{BARBER} {MANICURE} {NAIL} {SALON}] INSTRUMENTS AND TOOLS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Immerse pre-cleaned barber/salon instruments and tools {{InstrumentsTools}} in a use-solution of 1 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}} for at least 3 minutes. Rinse thoroughly and dry before use. Prepare a fresh solution daily or when visibly dirty.

SPLD_InsertTextSectionDU.Text: such as combs, brushes, razors, scissors, trimmer and/or clipper blades and manicure and pedicure instruments

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: TOILET BOWL AND URINAL DISINFECTANT/CLEANING
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: NON-ACID TOILET BOWL {{Urinal}} DISINFECTANT {{Cleaning}} DIRECTIONS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Remove heavy soil prior to disinfection.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: From a Concentrate:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: Add 0.6 oz. of this product directly into the water in the toilet bowl. Brush thoroughly over exposed surfaces and under the rim with a toilet {{BrushMop}}, cloth, or sponge. Allow solution to stand for 10 minutes and flush.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: From a Use Solution:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: Empty water out of toilet bowl or urinal and apply 0.5 to 1 oz. use solution to exposed surfaces, including under the rim with a toilet {{BrushMop}}, cloth, or sponge, {{SprayDevices}}.  {{SprayApplications}} Brush or swab thoroughly, then allow solution to stand for 10 minutes and flush.

SPLD_InsertTextDU.Text: {{HandPump}} coarse pump or trigger spray device.
For spray applications, spray 6-8 inches from surface. Do not breathe spray.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: HEAVY DUTY CLEANING OF TOILET BOWLS AND URNINALS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: FOR HEAVY DUTY CLEANING OF TOILET BOWLS AND URNINALS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Pre-clean heavily soiled areas. Empty toilet bowl or urinal and apply 1.2 oz. of this product to exposed surfaces including under the rim with toilet {{BrushMop}}, cloth, or sponge, or mechanical spray device, {{SprayDevices}}. To aid in soil removal, allow to soak. For sprayer application, spray 6-8 inches from surface. Brush or swab thoroughly and allow solution to stand for 10 minutes and flush.

SPLD_InsertTextSectionDU.Text: {{HandPump}} coarse pump or trigger spray device

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: DEEP CLEANING URINALS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: {{Deep}} CLEANING/DISINFECTING {{Waterless}} URINALS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Preliminary cleaning is required for heavily soiled surfaces. Remove and properly dispose of cartridge according to manufacturer?s directions. Deep clean or disinfect the entire urinal by applying 3 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}} directly onto surface. {{BrushScrub}} surfaces and let solution stand for 10 minutes. Wipe surface to clean. Change cartridge as needed. The unit is ready for use.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: CLEAN WATERLESS URINALS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: TO CLEAN WATERFREE {{Waterless}} URINALS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Remove any debris from the urinal. Spray 0.5 to 1 oz. of use solution onto urinal surface. To prepare use solution: add 0.6 oz. of this product per gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}} {{450PPM}}. DO NOT spray product directly onto cartridge. Wipe surface to clean. Change cartridge as needed. The unit is ready for use.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: CLEAN OPEN AREAS WITH FLOOR DRAINS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: FOR USE TO CLEAN AND DISINFECT SHOWER ROOMS, LOCKER ROOMS AND OTHER LARGE, OPEN AREAS WITH FLOOR DRAINS:

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: 1. Pre-clean heavily soiled areas.

2. Apply use solution of 3 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water {{450PPM}} {{EquivalentDilution}} to floors, walls and ceilings making sure not to over spray. To disinfect, all hard, non-porous surfaces must remain wet for 10 minutes.
3. Scrub using a deck brush or other coarse material as necessary.
4. Rinse surfaces thoroughly and let air dry.
5. Prepare a fresh solution daily or when visibly dirty.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: GENERAL CLEANER/DEODORIZER
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: FOR USE AS A {GENERAL} CLEANER {AND/OR DEODORIZER}:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Apply use solution of 1.75 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water to hard, non-porous surfaces. {{RinseWipeAirDry}}. For heavy-duty use, {{AddMix}} 4 oz. of this product per 5 gal. to clean hard, non-porous surfaces.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: GENERAL DEODORIZER
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: GENERAL DEODORIZATION
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: To deodorize, apply 1.75 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water to hard, non-porous surfaces. {{RinseWipeAirDry}}.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: SEPTIC STORAGE TANKS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: FOR DEODORIZING SEPTIC STORAGE TANKS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Pre-clean heavily soiled areas. When tanks are empty, pour 1.75 oz. of this product for every 5 gal. of water in tank on recreational vehicles, campers and boats to control odors. As tank fills with sewage and the vehicle is moving, this solution will mix and provide an adequate deodorizing solution for this use. This product is to be used on gray and black water tanks only. Check with local, state, or federal authorities before disposing of sewage in accordance to federal, state and local regulations for waste disposal. (Not for use in CA.)

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: RV HOLDING TANKS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: RV HOLDING TANKS/RECREATIONAL VEHICLES:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: For toilet waste and holding tanks, cover bottom of holding tank with water and add 1.75 to 3 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water to deodorize. If odors return before time to empty, add another 1.75 to 3 oz. per 5 gal. of water to the tank. For kitchen waste, add 1.75 to 3 oz. per 5 gal. of water to gray water tank as needed to control malodors created by dirty dishwater. (Not for use in CA.)

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: AUTOMOTIVE
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: AUTOMOTIVE USES:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: A solution of 1.75 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water will effectively neutralize {{DampMusty}} odors. Spray or apply onto seats, carpets, headliner and ashtray or into trunk and all vents to eliminate odors from tobacco, food, beverage spills and musty carpet. For sprayer applications, use a coarse spray device. {{WipeAirDry}}.  (Not for use in CA.)

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: AIR FRESHENER
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: AIR FRESHENER:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: A solution of 1.75 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water will effectively neutralize {{DampMusty}} odors caused by mildew in storage areas, basements, closets, bathrooms and A/C filters. Spray to eliminate odors from tobacco, food, beverage spills and musty carpet. For sprayer applications, use a coarse spray device. {{WipeAirDry}}.  (Not for use in CA.)

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: WATERBED CONDITIONER
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: WATERBED CONDITIONER (Not for use in CA.):
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: When used as a waterbed conditioner, this product eliminates odor. If bed has not been treated properly, drain bed completely. Add 15 gal. of water, mix vigorously, drain bed again. Fill bed with water and follow dosage directions.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: Dosage:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: To eliminate odor, add 4 ? 8 oz. of this product in a {{WavelessFree}} waterbed of 90 to 180 gal. capacity. Repeat application every 4 to 6 months.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: GLASS CLEANING
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: GLASS CLEANING {{Deodorizing}} DIRECTIONS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Use a 1.75 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water use solution to clean and deodorize windows, mirrors, and glass surfaces. Use a coarse spray device. For spray applications, spray 6-8 inches from surface. Do not breathe spray. Rub with sponge or cloth. Change cloth, sponge or towels frequently to avoid re-deposition of soil.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: FINISHED FLOORS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: FOR USE AS A CLEANER ON FINISHED FLOORS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: To limit gloss reduction, use 1.75 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water. Apply with a damp mop or auto scrubber. Allow surface to air dry.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: SPECIAL CARPET CLEANING
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: SPECIAL INSTRUCTIONS FOR CLEANING CARPETS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: This product can be used to clean carpets in industrial, institutional, commercial and residential areas such as homes, motel & hotel chains, nursing homes, schools and hospitals. For use on wet, cleanable synthetic fibers. Do not use on wool. Vacuum carpet thoroughly prior to cleaning. Test fabric for color fastness.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: Portable Extraction Units
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: For Portable Extraction Units:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Mix 1.1 oz. of this product per 1 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}}.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: Truck Mounted Extraction Machines
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: For Truck Mounted Extraction Machines:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Mix 1.1 oz. of this product per 1 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}} and meter at 5 gal. per hour

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: Rotary Floor Machines
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: For Rotary Floor Machines:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Mix 1.1 oz. of this product per 1 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}} and apply at the rate of 300-500 sq. ft. per 1 gal.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: Do not mix
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Do not mix this product with other cleaning products. Follow the cleaning procedures specified by the manufacturer of the cleaning equipment. After using this product set the carpet pile and protect the carpet from furniture legs and bases while drying. Do not over wet. If applied to stain resistant nylon carpet, apply a fabric protector according to the carpet manufacturer?s directions.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: CARPET HOME
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: CARPET {{Cleaning/Deodorizing}} FOR HOME, INSTITUTIONAL, INDUSTRIAL AND HOSPITAL USE:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: This product {{CleansDeodorizes}} the carpet. It can be used in industrial, institutional, commercial and residential areas such as homes, motels, hotel chains, nursing homes and hospitals.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: Vacuum carpet thoroughly
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Vacuum carpet thoroughly prior to application. Mix 1.1 oz. per gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}}. Follow the injection and/or extraction procedures as specified for any conventional steam cleaning equipment you are using. For rotary floor machines, mix 1.1 oz. of this product per gal. of water and spray on carpet at a rate of 300-500 sq. ft. per 1 gal.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: Washable synthetic fibers
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: {{Use}} on washable synthetic fibers. Do not use on wool. Test color fastness of carpet before use. Apply diluted product to a small concealed spot, then rub with a clean white cloth. If color changes or transfers to the cloth, a water-based product must not be used.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: After using
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: After using the product, set carpet pile in one direction with a stiff brush. Place aluminum foil under the legs of furniture while carpet is drying. Over-wetting can cause carpet to shrink. Manufacturer assumes no responsibility for over-wetting misuse.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: SEWER BACKUP & RIVER FLOODING
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: SEWER BACKUP & RIVER FLOODING:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: To use as a deodorizer, dilute 1.1 to 2.2 oz. of this product per gal. of water allowing for the diluting effect of absorbed water within saturated materials. Remove gross filth or heavy soil along with non-salvageable materials. Saturate all affected areas with a mechanical spray device, {{CoarsePumpTriggerSprayDevice}} before and after cleaning and extraction. For spray applications, spray 6-8 inches from surface. Do not breathe spray. Use proper ventilation; open windows. (Not for use in CA.)

SPLD_InsertTextSectionDU.Text: coarse pump or trigger spray device

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: POROUS MATERIALS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: CARPETS, CARPET CUSHIONS, UPHOLSTERY, DRAPES AND OTHER POROUS MATERIALS, SUB FLOORS, DRYWALL, TRIM AND FRAME LUMBER, TACKLESS STRIP AND PANELING:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: To use as a deodorizer against water damage, extract the excess water. Test hidden area for colorfastness. Dilute 1.1 to 2.2 oz. of this product per gal. of water, allowing for the diluting effect of absorbed water within saturated materials. Remove gross filth or heavy soil. Apply directly with a mechanical spray device {or coarse pump or trigger spray device} to fully saturate affected materials. For spray applications, spray 6-8 inches from surface. Do not breathe spray. Roll, brush or agitate into materials. Follow with a thorough extraction. Dry rapidly and thoroughly. (Not for use in CA.)

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: WATER/SMOKE DAMAGE
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: {{WaterSmoke}} DAMAGE RESTORATION:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Effective against odor caused by smoke and water damage for home, institutional, industrial and hospital use. This product is particularly suitable for use in water damage restoration. Dilute 1.1 to 2.2 oz. of this product per gal. of water, allowing for the diluting effect of absorbed water within saturated materials. Saturate affected materials with enough product to remain wet for at least 10 minutes. Use proper ventilation. (Not for use in CA.)

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: DROSOPHILA SPP. AND PHORIDAE FAMILY OF FLIES
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: FOR CONTROL OF DROSOPHILA SPP. AND PHORIDAE FAMILY OF FLIES ON NON-FOOD CONTACT SURFACES:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: To control flies on hard, non-porous non-food contact surfaces such as floors, walls, countertops, metal surfaces, painted surfaces, glazed porcelain, glazed tile, glass, chrome, rubber, and plastic in restaurants, bars, kitchens, dishwashing areas, and bar and wait station areas and other food storage areas. After removing gross filth, apply a solution of {{3oz}} of this product per 5 gal. of water {{EquivalentUse}} to surfaces and locations where flies breed. Spray surfaces thoroughly or apply by pouring, mopping or sponging onto the surface. Allow surface to remain wet for 10 minutes. Repeat application 1-2 times per week or as needed. Do not contaminate food and food packaging.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: SMALL FLIES IN DRAINS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: FOR CONTROL OF SMALL FLIES IN DRAINS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: For control of small flies: Drosophila spp. and the Phoridae family. Spray or pour solution of {{3oz}} of this product per 5 gal. of water {{EquivalentUse}} into the drain during time of lowest level of drain use. Add 14 oz. of use solution daily to each drain to maintain fly control. Apply product around the edge of the drain and thoroughly coat inside of drain. Repeat application 1-2 times per week or as needed. Do not contaminate food and food packaging.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: Site Preparation:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: The first step in any ongoing sanitation program must be the removal of gross contamination and debris. This may be accomplished by using a shovel, broom, or vacuum, depending on the area to be disinfected.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: Disinfection:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: For heavily soiled areas, pre-clean first. Use {{3Oz}} of this product per 5 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}} use solution. Wet all hard, non-porous surfaces thoroughly. Treated surfaces must remain wet for 10 minutes. Let air-dry. Prepare a fresh solution for each use.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: For Heavy Duty Cleaning:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: When heavy duty cleaning is desired, use 6 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water {{1.25Oz}} {{EquivalentDilution}}. Heavily soiled areas will require repeated cleaning before treatment.

SPLD_InsertTextDU.Text: (1.25 oz. of this product per gal. of water)

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: DO NOT APPLY TO THE MUSHROOM CROP, COMPOST OR CASING.
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: Rinse treated surfaces with potable water before they contact the crop, compost or casing.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: CITRUS CANKER CONTROL
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: CITRUS CANKER CONTROL (Not For Use in CA):
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: For prevention of Citrus Canker Disease through treatment of pre-cleaned equipment. Effective against Xanthomonas axonopodis pv. citri {{CitrusCanker}} at 2000 ppm active. Treatment can be applied to trucks, attached trailers, field harvesting equipment, including cargo area, wheels, tires, undercarriage, hood, roof, fenders and any other hard, non-porous part of equipment that can be taken into infested areas. Thoroughly clean all surfaces with soap or detergent and rinse with water. Then saturate surfaces with a use dilution of 2.5 oz. of this product per gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}} {{2000PPM}} for a period of 10 minutes. Allow to air dry. All surfaces that come in contact with food or crop must be rinsed with potable water before reuse. To prevent the spread of Citrus Canker Disease by this artificial means of transportation, treatments are made by trigger spraying, dipping or brushing. Clothing must be either thoroughly rinsed or laundered before reuse. Footwear must be rinsed before reuse. Prepare a fresh solution daily or when visibly dirty

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: WHIRLPOOL UNITS DISINFECTION/VIRUCIDE*
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: DISINFECTION/VIRUCIDE* OF HARD, NON-POROUS SURFACES IN WHIRLPOOL UNITS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: After using the whirlpool unit, drain unit. Prepare a use solution of 3 oz. of the product per 5 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}} and refill with use solution to just cover intake valves {{2InchesAboveHighestJet}}. Briefly start the pump to circulate the solution. Turn off the pump. Wash down the unit sides, seat of the chair lift and any other related equipment with a clean swab, brush or sponge. Treated surfaces must remain wet for 10 minutes. After the unit has been thoroughly disinfected, drain the solution from the unit and rinse disinfected surfaces with fresh water. Wipe dry with a clean sponge or cloth or allow to air dry. Repeat for heavy soiled units.

SPLD_InsertTextSectionDU.Text: or 2 inches above the highest jet

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: WHIRLPOOL UNITS SANITIZATION
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: SANITIZATION OF HARD, NON-POROUS SURFACES IN WHIRLPOOL UNITS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: To remove body oils, dead tissue, soil and all other buildups or organic matter on surfaces after using the whirlpool unit, drain unit. Prepare a use solution of 0.25 oz. of this product per gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}} and refill with use solution to just cover the intake valves {{2InchesAboveHighestJet}}. Briefly start the pump to circulate the solution. Turn off the pump. Wash down the unit sides, seat of the chair lift and any other related equipment with a clean swab, brush or sponge. Treated surfaces must remain wet for 3 minutes. After the unit has been thoroughly sanitized, drain the solution from the unit and rinse all with fresh water. Repeat for heavy soiled units. Then the unit is ready for reuse.

SPLD_InsertTextSectionDU.Text: or 2 inches above the highest jet

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: BAGLESS VACUUM CLEANERS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: FOR DISINFECTING BAGLESS VACUUM CLEANERS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Add 3 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}}. Turn off and unplug vacuum cleaner. Remove the hard, non-porous container that houses collected material from the vacuum cleaner. Empty contents into a waste receptacle. Rinse collection container with water and wipe clean to remove any additional collected material. Apply use solution to collection container with a brush, cloth, mop, sponge, mechanical spray device, {{{SprayDevices}} so as to wet all surfaces thoroughly. {{SprayerApplications}} Allow surfaces to remain wet for 10 minutes. Wipe up excess liquid with a clean cloth or sponge or allow to air dry. Reattach container to vacuum cleaner.

SPLD_InsertTextSectionDU.Text: {{Pump}} coarse pump or trigger spray device
For sprayer applications, spray 6-8 inches from surface.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: VACUUM CLEANER BRUSHES
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: FOR DISINFECTING NON-POROUS VACUUM CLEANER BRUSHES:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Add 3 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}}. Turn off and unplug vacuum cleaner. Remove the non-porous brushes from vacuum cleaner. Submerge brush in use solution so as to wet all surfaces thoroughly. Allow surfaces to remain wet for 10 minutes. Wipe up excess liquid with a clean cloth or sponge or allow to air dry. Reattach brushes to vacuum cleaner.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: COMMERCIAL FLORIST
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: COMMERCIAL FLORIST USE DIRECTIONS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: To clean, disinfect {{Deodorize}} hard, non-porous surfaces, prepare use solution of 1.75 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}}. For heavy-duty use, add 4 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}}. Remove all leaves, petals, garbage and refuse. Pre-clean surfaces using pressurized water where possible. Apply use solution to hard, non-porous surfaces, thoroughly wetting surfaces as required, with a cloth, mop, brush, sponge, {{AutoScrubber,}} or mechanical spray device, {{SprayDevices}}. For sprayer applications, spray 6-8 inches from surface. Rub with brush, sponge, mop or cloth. Do not breathe spray. Treated surfaces must remain wet for 10 minutes. Wipe up excess or allow to air dry. Change cloth, sponge or towels frequently to avoid re-deposition of soil. Prepare a fresh solution daily or when visibly dirty.

SPLD_InsertTextSectionDU.Text: {{Pump}}} coarse pump or trigger spray device

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: WORK AREAS AND BENCHES
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: WORK AREAS AND BENCHES, POTS, FLATS AND FLOWER BUCKETS, CUTTING TOOLS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Pre-clean surfaces. {{SpraySwabSoak}} with a solution of 1.75 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}} before each work period and again after each plant is completed {{ControlDiseaseTransfer}}. Allow surface to remain wet for 10 minutes. To apply solution as a sprayer application, use as a coarse spray only and spray 6-8 inches from surface. Wipe up excess liquid or allow to air dry. {{DryOilTools}} Prepare a fresh solution daily or when visibly dirty. (?Not for use in CA.)

SPLD_InsertTextSectionDU.Text: to help control transfer of diseases such as Botrytis, crown rot, downy mildew, Erwinia and root rot?
Dry and oil tools at the end of each workday.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: CLEANSING OF EXTERIOR BODY SURFACES
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: CLEANSING OF EXTERIOR BODY SURFACES OF {{HumanRemains}}:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: To cleanse away skin secretions and accompanying malodor, to ensure the removal of all soil and bloodstains, and to remove and reduce surface contamination, apply 1.75 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}} to the exterior surfaces of the body. Bathe the entire body using sponge or washcloth. A soft brush may be employed on surfaces other than the face. Allow a 10 minute contact time for optimal results. Prepare a fresh solution for each human remain.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: KITCHEN/BATHROOM/HOUSEHOLD
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: CLEAN/DISINFECT/DEODORIZE {{KitchenBathroomHousehold}} SURFACES:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Pre-clean surfaces. Apply a solution of 3 oz. of this product per 5 gal. of water {{EquivalentDilution}} with brush, cloth, mop, sponge, mechanical spray device, {{SprayDevices}}. For spray applications, hold container 6 to 8 inches from surface and spray until thoroughly wet. For disinfection, treated surfaces must remain wet for 10 minutes. Wipe up excess liquid or allow to air dry. Rinse with potable water after use on surfaces that come in contact with food. SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: SANITIZATION OF EXTERIOR HOUSEHOLD SURFACES DIRECTIONS

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: Preparation of Use Solution:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: Apply a use solution of 0.25 oz. of this product per gal. of water {{200PPM}} {{EquivalentDilution}} to sanitize hard, non-porous exterior surfaces such as vinyl, plastic, sealed concrete, painted or sealed woodwork, and sealed stucco. Surfaces to be treated include house siding, decks, patios, walkways and driveways.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: Application:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: Pre-clean heavily soiled areas. Apply solution with a brush, mop, cloth, sponge, {{AutoScrubber,}} mechanical spray device, {{SprayDevices}}, or with a low-pressure {{LessThan60PSI}} airless sprayer so as to wet all surfaces thoroughly. For sprayer applications, spray 6 inches to 8 inches from surface. Treated surfaces must remain wet for 3 minutes. Wearing suitable respiratory protective equipment and protective eyewear to control exposure to spray, pressure wash surfaces to thoroughly sanitize all treated areas using a high-pressure spray. Do not breathe spray. One-half gal. of diluted product will treat 200-300 sq. ft. of surface. Prepare a fresh solution daily or when visibly dirty.

SPLD_InsertTextDU.Text: {{Pump}}} coarse pump or trigger spray device

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: LAUNDRY
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: COMMERCIAL AND INSTITUTIONAL LAUNDRY USE:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: For residual bacteriostatic activity against gram negative and/or gram positive odor-causing bacteria and/or residual self-sanitizing activity against Klebsiella pneumoniae and Staphylococcus aureus, use this product as directed.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: Initial Treatment
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: Initial Treatment:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Use 10 oz. of this product per 100 pounds of fabric (dry weight) {{EquivalentDilution}}. Dilute the appropriate amount of this product in one to two gal. of water, and then add solution to the wash wheel at the beginning of the final rinse cycle. A minimum rinse cycle time of 5 minutes is required

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: Repeat Treatment
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: Repeat Treatment:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Repeat Treatment: Follow Initial Treatment directions and re-treat fabric after each washing {{IfOdorPersists}}.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: LAUNDRY BACTERIOSTAT
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: LAUNDRY BACTERIOSTAT FOR COMMERCIAL, INDUSTRIAL, AND NON-MEDICAL INSTITUTIONAL LAUNDRY APPLICATIONS:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: This product provides the fabric with residual bacteriostatic activity against odor causing gram-negative and gram-positive bacteria when added to the final rinse at a rate of 10 oz. of this product per 100 lbs. of dry laundry. This product was evaluated against:  Corynebacterium ammoniagenes {{ATCC6872}} Klebsiella pneumoniae {{ATCC4352}} Staphylococcus aureus {{ATCC6538}}

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: LAUNDRY DEODORIZER
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: LAUNDRY DEODORIZER {AGAINST ODOR CAUSING BACTERIA}:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: For activity against odor causing bacteria caused by conditions of high relative humidity or wet contamination, use 12 oz. of this product per 100 pounds of dry weight fabric. Dilute the appropriate amount of this product in one to two gal. of water, and then add to the wash wheel in the final rinse. Re-treat fabric after each washing. Laundered fabric may also be treated by soaking.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: PRESERVATION AGAINST MILDEW
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: PRESERVATION AGAINST MILDEW BY SOAKING:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Use 10 oz. of this product per 100 pounds of fabric (dry weight). A minimum soaking time of 5 minutes is required.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: LAUNDRY SANITIZER
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: LAUNDRY SANITIZER:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: When added at the rate of 1 oz. of this product per gal. water {{Yield780PPM}} {{12Oz}} {{EquivalentDilution}} {{780PPM}}, this formulation provides sanitization against Staphylococcus aureus, Klebsiella pneumoniae, Pseudomonas aeruginosa, and Staphylococcus aureus Methicillin Resistant (MRSA) and is effective against HIV-1 in rinse water up to 200 ppm hard water.

SPLD_InsertTextSectionDU.Text: (12 oz. of this product per 100 lbs. of dry laundry)

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: KILLS HIV-1 ON LAUNDRY
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: KILLS HIV-1 ON LAUNDRY IN COMMERCIAL, INDUSTRIAL AND INSTITUTIONAL APPLICATIONS.
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: This product provides virucidal* activity against HIV-1 on fabrics when presoaked with a 4 minute contact time followed by normal washing in detergent and rinsing at a rate of 12 oz. of this product per 100 lbs. of dry laundry in water hardness up to 200 ppm.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: LAUNDRY SANITIZING
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: LAUNDRY SANITIZING DIRECTIONS FOR USE:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: For sanitizing step, fill washer to low water level with minimum temperature water of 95F. Using an appropriate {{#CompanyName}}} dispenser, inject this product into the sanitizing rinse step at the rate of 1 oz. of this product per gal. water {{Yield780PPM}} {{12Oz}} {{780PPM}} {{EquivalentDilution}}. Treat the laundry for a minimum of 5 minutes at a minimum temperature of 95F. Other laundry additives, such as fabric softeners, laundry sours, starch and sizing must be used per manufacturer?s instructions in subsequent rinse cycles after the sanitizing rinse cycle.

SPLD_InsertTextSectionDU.Text: (12 oz. of this product per 100 lbs. of dry laundry)

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: LAUNDRY FINAL CYCLE
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: LAUNDRY SANITIZING DIRECTIONS FOR USE:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: This product is used in the final, warm rinse cycle at a low water level. Dilute at 1 oz. of this product per gal. of water {{12Oz}} {{780PPM}} {{EquivalentDilution}}, then add to the wash in the final rinse, or dispense directly through automatic dispensing equipment. Run for a minimum of 5 minutes. Retreat as necessary. This product will not harm fabrics. DO NOT USE IN THE PRESENCE OF, OR MIX WITH OTHER CHEMICALS.

SPLD_InsertTextSectionDU.Text: (12 oz. of this product per 100 lbs. of dry laundry)

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: RECIRCULATING COOLING WATER TOWERS
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: INDUSTRIAL {{AND/OR} COMMERCIAL} RECIRCULATING COOLING WATER TOWERS, RETORT WATER SYSTEMS (Not for use in CA.)
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle:
Cooling tower waters that are inherently low in algae growth and bacteria count may be adequately controlled by the lower range of these dosages. Repeat every seven days or increase frequency if needed. Should slime develop again, repeat initial dosage.

For best results, clean heavily contaminated systems before treatment with this product. If soap or anionic detergent is used, rinse thoroughly before charging with this algaecide.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: 1. Dosing Location:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: This product is to be applied at a point in the system where it will be uniformly mixed, such as at the sump.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: 2. Dosing Conditions:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: This product must be applied when the system is in jeopardy of being affected or after cleaning systems where efficiency is already impaired. Tower bleed off valves must be closed to permit a retention time of 4 hours.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: a. INTERMITTENT OR SLUG METHOD
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text:
Initial Dose: When the system is noticeably fouled, apply 26.25 fl. oz. of this product {(20 ppm on an active basis)} per 1,000 gal. of water in the system.

Subsequent Dose: When microbial control is evident, add 6.65 to 19.25 fl. oz. of this product per 1,000 gal. of water in the system weekly or as needed to maintain control.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: b. MODIFIED INTERMITTENT METHOD
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text:
Initial Dose: When the system is noticeably fouled, apply 26.25 fl. oz. of this product {(20 ppm on an active basis)} per 1,000 gal. of water in the system. Apply half of this initial dose when half of the water in the system has been lost by blowdown.

Subsequent Dose: When control of microbial growth is evident, apply 6.65 to 19.25 fl. oz. of this product per 1,000 gal. of water in the system. Apply half of this subsequent dose when half of the water in the system has been lost by blowdown.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: c. CONTINUOUS FEED METHOD
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text:
Initial Dose: When the system is noticeably fouled, apply 26.25. of this product {(20 ppm on an active basis)} per 1,000 gal. of water in the system.

Subsequent Dose: Maintain this treatment by starting a continuous feed of 6.65 to 19.25 fl. oz. of this product per 1,000 gal. of water lost by blowdown.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: ONCE THROUGH WATER COOLING SYSTEM
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: ONCE THROUGH FRESH {{AndSea}} WATER COOLING SYSTEM (Not for use in CA.)
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle:
Use of the product in either public/municipal or single or multiple family private/residential potable/drinking water systems is strictly prohibited. Use of the product in any cooling water system that discharges effluent within 0.25 mile of either a public/municipal or single or multiple family private/residential potable/drinking water intake is strictly prohibited.

For best results, slug feed. The frequency of addition of microbiocide needed depends on many factors. To optimize your use of water treatment microbiocide, follow this procedure.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: 1. Dosing Location:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: This product is to be applied at a point in the system where it will be uniformly mixed, such as at the sump.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: 2. Dosing Conditions:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: This product must be applied when the system is in jeopardy of being affected or after cleaning systems where efficiency is already impaired.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: a.
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: Wear safety glasses, rubber gloves and impervious apron

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: b.
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: To reduce foaming, mix 10 parts of water to 1 part of this product

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: c.
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: {{UseAdd}} 0.75 to 7 fl. oz. of this product {{0.6-6PPM}} per 1,000 gal.

SPLD_InsertTextDU.Text: (0.6 to 6 ppm on an active basis)

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: d.
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: Do not discharge without performing proper deactivation.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: e.
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: Treatment time cannot exceed 120 hours/application nor exceed 4 times per year.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: f.
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: Avoid oxidizers and reducing agents. Product is cationic and must not be mixed with soap or anionic surfactants

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: 3. Method Of Application:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: INTERMITTENT OR SLUG METHOD
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.ReviewerNote: Alternate Method of Application language can be used in place of Item #3 directly above.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: Initial Dose:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: When the system is noticeably fouled, apply 0.75 to 7 fl. oz. of this product {(0.6 to 6 ppm on an active basis)} per 1,000 gal. of water based on system flow rates. The minimum treatment is 6 to 24 hours. Repeat until control is achieved. Deactivation must be conducted prior to discharge from the system by using bentonite clay at a minimum ratio of 5 ppm clay to 1 ppm product.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Title: Subsequent Dose:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: When microbial control is evident, add 0.375 to 3.75 fl. oz. of this product {(0.3 to 3 ppm on an active basis)} per 1,000 gal. of water based upon system flow rates on an as needed basis to maintain control. Frequency of feed must be tied to an in-plant monitoring program for macro cowling growth. Deactivation must be conducted prior to discharge from the system by using bentonite clay at a minimum ratio of 5 ppm clay to 1 ppm product.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: DEACTIVATION
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: DEACTIVATION:
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: Use bentonite clay at the minimum ratio of 5 ppm clay to 1 ppm product. This product must be deactivated prior to discharge of the NPDES outfall. Do not apply this product more than 4 times a year.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Name: OILFIELD INJECTION AND WASTE WATER
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Title: OILFIELD INJECTION AND WASTE WATER (Not for use in CA.):
SPLD_DirectionsForUseSection.Subtitle: This product must be added to the water handling system at a point of uniform mixing such as the area of addition of makeup water to the holding tank.

SPLD_DirectionsForUseStatement.Text: Continuous Injection: Add this product at 30 ppm {(22.5 fl. oz. of this product per 1,000 gal. of water)} when system is noticeably fouled. When microbial control is evident, add this product at 15 ppm (30 fl. oz. of this product per 1,000 gal. of water) to maintain control.

Batch Treatment: Add this product at 180 ppm {(230 fl. oz. of this product per 1,000 gal. of water)} over a period of 4-6 hours one or more times per week when the system is noticeably fouled. When microbial control is evident, add this product at 90 ppm (115 fl. oz. of this product per 1,000 gal. of water) over a period of 4-6 hours one or more time per week.
